The paper discusses automated termination proof methods for higher-order calculi, which is a topic related to logic and computation. Therefore, cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with recursive path ordering, which is a technique used in programming language theory and type theory, making cs.PL (Programming Languages) and cs.TL (Type Theory) likely sub-categories as well. Additionally, the paper discusses computability arguments, which are related to theoretical computer science, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper may also be relevant to cs.SE (Software Engineering) as it discusses automated termination proof methods.
